The paper deals with information theory and communication channels, specifically the Gaussian Dirty Tape Channel and the Gaussian multiple access channel with additive interference. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses compensation strategies and achievable rate regions, which are related to optimization and machine learning, respectively, making cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible sub-categories. The paper also considers the impact of interference on the channels, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
